  "commentary": "With SPX at 6817.38 sitting above the GEX flip at 6799, dealers are in positive gamma territory and will mechanically sell into any further rally while buying dips, creating stabilizing pressure around current levels. The massive +5053.5M gamma wall at 6900 represents strong dealer selling pressure that should cap upside momentum, while the regime suggests mean reversion behavior rather than trending moves. Key levels to watch: 6799 flip strike as critical support/resistance, 6900 as the primary upside magnet where dealer selling intensifies, and 6820 which holds significant stabilizing gamma near current spot.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pulled toward 6900 but face strong resistance there, with overall choppy action between 6800-6900.",
